ps = range(0, 4)
d=1
qs = range(0, 1)
Ps = range(0, 3)
D=2
Qs = range(0, 3)

parameters = product(ps, qs, Ps, Qs)
parameters_list = list(parameters)
len(parameters_list)

In [ ]:
%%time
results = []
best_aic = float("inf")

warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

for param in tqdm(parameters_list):
    #try except is needed because some parameter combinations are not valid
    try:
        model=sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(christmas_df, order=(param[0], d, param[1]), 
                                        seasonal_order=(param[2], D, 
                                                        param[3], week_period)).fit(disp=-1)
    except ValueError:
        print('wrong parameters:', param)
        continue
    aic = model.aic
    # save best model, it's AIC and params
    if aic < best_aic:
        best_model = model
        best_aic = aic
        best_param = param
    results.append([param, model.aic])
